    <div class="content-wrapper">
        <!-- Left box: Instructions -->
        <div class="box instructions-box">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <p>This is a web framework that can be used to compare two algorithms. A dataset in the form of a CSV file needs to be uploaded, and the two algorithms to compare need to be added as Python code.</p>
            <h3>Format for CSV File:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>CSV file should have two columns, namely <b>x</b> and <b>y</b>.</li>
                <li>Ensure that both <b>x</b> and <b>y</b> contain valid numbers only.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Format for Python File:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>The Python file should accept data points as input.</li>
                <li>It must return an image using: <code>plt.savefig('uploads/algorithm1_result.png')</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

